          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "DATA-ERR",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                ". The total error of the cross sections was",
                "derived as the square root of the sum of square of the",
                "individual errors.",
                "-flux measurement: 8%",
                "-detector efficiency and counting geometry: 5%",
                "-decay data: 3%",
                "-counting statistics: less than 1%",
                "typical overall error 10%",
                " (en-err). Main error source in the energy scale:",
                "-energy spread of the incident beam: +-0.2 MeV",
                "-foil thickness: 0.001%",
                "-energy straggling: calculated with trim-92 (monte-",
                "           carlo calculation)",
                "-energy-range calculation: 5%",
                "the estimated error of the energy scale: +-0.22 MeV",
                "at 18. MeV and +- 0.6 MeV at 5 MeV."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ADD-RES": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "compilation and critical comparision and evalution of",
                "the excitation functions of Fe-nat(p,xn)Co-56 reaction",
                "measured between 1959-1993 is given. Check of the",
                "feasibility and the predictability of the recomended",
                "data set via reproduction of calibration curves for",
                "thin layer activation technique."
              ]
            }
          ],
